briefdescription.para: Constructs a BCardView from an archive message.

detaileddescription.para: This method is usually not called directly, if you want to build a card view from an archived message you should call Instantiate() instead because it can handle errors properly.

parameterdescription.para: The BMessage that contains the card view.

briefdescription.para: Creates a new card view with the given name.

parameterdescription.para: The name for the card view.

briefdescription.para: Get a pointer to the underlying BCardLayout.

simplesect.para: A pointer to the underlying card layout.

parameterdescription.para: The layout to set to. This must be a BCardLayout, or a derivative. Any other layout types will be ignored.

briefdescription.para: Instantiate the view from the message from.
Container view for a stack of alternating child views.

detaileddescription.para: This class is a convencience class, that creates a BView with a BCardLayout set up by default.

The card container holds zero or more child views and organizes them like a stack of cards. Each child view is a card, and only one card can be on top, meaning that it is visible and available for interaction by the user. When there are no cards, or no card is on top, then the system's default gray background is displayed.

simplesect.para: BCardLayout for more information on how and when to use this type of container.
